  "doc_id": "prion_0563",
  "text": "The authors present an analysis of the clinical course of 6 cases of Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease (patients were aged from 27 to 59 years).\nThe diagnosis was established during the life of the patients.\nIn the neurological status dementia and syndromes of pyramidal and extrapyramidal lesions predominated.\nNeuropathological examinations in 5 cases demonstrated also considerable cerebellar damage, however, clinical signs of this damage were noted in two patients only.\nEEG findings were of greatest importance among the laboratory investigations.",
